# Market Digest — Cursor Rules

## What This Project Is
A daily market intelligence repo using a 7-phase AI-orchestrated pipeline. Skill files (`skills/*.md`) are step-by-step instruction sets for AI agents. Memory files (`memory/*/ROLLING.md`) are append-only research logs.

## Core Architecture
- `skills/SKILL-orchestrator.md` — master pipeline (read this first for context)
- `config/watchlist.md` + `config/preferences.md` — user configuration (read at session start)
- `memory/BIAS-TRACKER.md` — daily cross-asset bias log (14 columns)
- `outputs/daily/YYYY-MM-DD/` — one folder per day, 22 output files

## Skill File Rules
When editing `skills/*.md` files:
- YAML frontmatter `name:` and `description:` are sacred — do NOT rename without updating `CLAUDE_PROJECT_INSTRUCTIONS.md`
- Always preserve `## Memory Update` heading and its content
- Output paths use `{{DATE}}` placeholder — never hardcode dates
- Keep numbered Steps format: `### 1. Step Name` throughout

## Memory File Rules
Files in `memory/*/ROLLING.md` are APPEND-ONLY:
- Never delete, rewrite, or reorder existing entries
- Add new entries at the END of the file
- Format: `## YYYY-MM-DD` header followed by 3-5 bullet points

## Script Rules
- All scripts: `#!/bin/bash` + `set -e` at top
- macOS sed: use `sed -i ""` NOT `sed -i` (critical — macOS incompatibility otherwise)
- All paths are relative to repo root
- Search memory subdirs with `find memory/ -name "ROLLING.md"` not `memory/*/ROLLING.md`

## Output Rules
- outputs/daily/ is AGENT-GENERATED — do not manually edit these files
- New day folder: `outputs/daily/YYYY-MM-DD/` with `sectors/` subfolder
- Master output: `outputs/daily/YYYY-MM-DD/DIGEST.md`

## Markdown Standards
- Headings: `#` then `##` then `###` — never skip levels
- Tables: always include `|---|---|` separator row
- Templates use `{{PLACEHOLDER}}` syntax for runtime substitution

## Forbidden Actions
- Do NOT delete memory file content
- Do NOT modify `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` or `weekly-check.yml` without understanding CI/CD
- Do NOT change skill frontmatter `name:` fields without cascading updates

## Documentation Index
- `CLAUDE.md` — Claude Code reference
- `AGENTS.md` — Cross-platform agent reference
- `docs/agentic/` — Full documentation suite
- `docs/agentic/ARCHITECTURE.md` — System design
- `docs/agentic/SKILLS-CATALOG.md` — All 35+ skills indexed
